# Project Agent Skills (required workflow)

This repository vendors Agent Skills under `.agents/skills/`. The pinned set and sources are recorded in `skills-lock.json` at the repo root.

## When to read which skill

Before making **non-trivial** changes, **read the relevant `SKILL.md` first** (use the Read tool), then follow it for the rest of that task:

| Skill | Path | Use when |
| --- | --- | --- |
| Next.js best practices | `.agents/skills/next-best-practices/SKILL.md` | App Router files, RSC boundaries, async APIs, routing, metadata, errors |
| Vercel React best practices | `.agents/skills/vercel-react-best-practices/SKILL.md` | React/Next performance, data fetching, bundle size, rerenders |
| Web Interface Guidelines | `.agents/skills/web-design-guidelines/SKILL.md` | UI/UX review, accessibility, interaction polish |
| shadcn/ui | `.agents/skills/shadcn/SKILL.md` | Adding or changing UI components, forms, dialogs, charts, styling tokens |
| Node.js backend patterns | `.agents/skills/nodejs-backend-patterns/SKILL.md` | Route Handlers, server modules, validation, caching, security boundaries |
| TypeScript advanced types | `.agents/skills/typescript-advanced-types/SKILL.md` | Shared types, generics, inference-heavy or financial-domain modeling |
| Playwright best practices | `.agents/skills/playwright-best-practices/SKILL.md` | E2E tests, fixtures, locators, CI |
| Frontend design (Anthropic) | `.agents/skills/frontend-design/SKILL.md` | **Optional**: distinctive marketing or one-off surfaces; avoid fighting shadcn on core app chrome |
| UI/UX Pro Max | `.agents/skills/ui-ux-pro-max/SKILL.md` | Layout/flow heuristics; defer to shadcn + Web Guidelines when they conflict |

## Depth rules

- **Vercel React**: for a specific issue (e.g. waterfall), open the matching rule file under `.agents/skills/vercel-react-best-practices/rules/` as needed.
- **Next**: follow links from `SKILL.md` to the referenced `.md` files in the same folder.
- **shadcn**: use the project shadcn CLI and aliases from `web/components.json` once initialized; do not guess component APIs—use `npx shadcn@latest docs …` per the skill.

## Do not relocate skills casually

Keep skill content in **`.agents/skills/`** so `skills-lock.json` stays the single inventory. If tooling ever requires `.cursor/skills/`, prefer **documentation + rules** (this file) rather than duplicating skill trees.
